INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (3919,407,'layouts_0_text1','quantum was in charge of planning and managing the \"Android Experiments OBJECT\", “a project to create devices that will make the world more convenient and fun by connecting to Android with everyone\'s ideas”. We have supported the process of selecting ideas to creating prototypes.\r\n\r\nAndroid was developed as an open-source mobile platform to allow developers and companies around the world to create mobile devices based on their own ideas. This project was created not only to convey the idea of Android, but also to support the free ideas of people from all walks of life, including product designers, start-ups, and students.\r\n\r\nMore than 200 ideas were gathered from all over Japan. The four ideas were selected by advisors and online public voting with approximately 19,000 votes. The completed prototypes were experienced by 17,000 people during a four-week exhibition and were covered by numerous Japanese and international media.\r\n\r\n\r\nHere are the four ideas that were prototyped.\r\n');
